external_knowledge:
- Junctions refer to intersections;
- Specific signal types relate to the type of traffic signals (e.g., 2-phase, 3-phase);
- The counts are the total number of signals at each intersection and the number of specific types of signals at those intersections.

- "bustling traffic" refers to the traffic volume, speed, and occupancy details;
- "measurements were taken" corresponds to the time stamp of the data collection;
- "how many vehicles passed" relates to the traffic volume in vehicles per hour;
- "how fast they were moving" refers to the speed in miles per hour;
- "how crowded the area was" pertains to the traffic occupancy as a percentage;
- "sensor captured this information" indicates the ID of the sensor that collected the data;
- "how reliable the data is" refers to the quality of the traffic data.

